summary: With a career spanning nearly two decades in the dental industry, I am a dedicated professional with a diverse skill set and a passion for continuous learning. Starting my journey in 2004, I have since immersed myself in various roles across the sector, balancing my time between clinical and non-clinical responsibilities. This approach has enabled me to broaden my expertise, contributing to both public and private health entities.My enthusiasm for the dental field extends to the training and development of other practitioners. I have been involved in teaching accredited and non-accredited courses for the NSW government and private training institutes, sharing my knowledge and experience with aspiring dental professionals.As an expert in management and policy implementation, I have played a pivotal role in assisting dental practices in Sydney and regional areas of NSW to achieve accreditation. My commitment to excellence and leadership is further demonstrated through my positions as a Board Director for the Indigenous Dental Association of Australia and the DHAA Inc.Currently, I am a postgraduate student at the University of Melbourne, pursuing a DDS program with a keen interest in Dental Sleep Medicine. This marks my fourth and final degree, underscoring my dedication to lifelong learning in the field of dentistry. Additionally, I am a candidate for the Master Fellow award with the American Academy of Oral Systemic Health, aiming to achieve this prestigious recognition by the end of 2024.In addition to my academic pursuits, I own a private practice in regional NSW, where I continue to apply my skills and knowledge to provide high-quality dental care. My commitment to the dental industry is further evidenced by my roles as an Authorised Supervisor & Mentor for the Dental Council of NSW, an Assessor for the Australian Dental Council, an Honorary Clinical Fellow at the University of Melbourne, and a Lecturer at La Trobe University.My qualifications include a Bachelor of Oral Health, a Bachelor of Oral Health Therapy – ES, a Graduate Diploma in Cosmetic Dermal Science, a Professional Certificate in Integrated Health & Dermatology, and a Fellowship with the American Academy of Oral Systemic Health (FAAOSH). I hold a Clinical Fellowship at the University of Melbourne School of Dentistry and Medicine. Additionally, I have a Diploma in Practice Management and a Certificate IV in Training & Assessment.As I continue my journey in the dental industry, I remain committed to advancing my knowledge and providing exceptional care to my patients

I am expanding my private practice to 4 chairs and urgently require interest from Dental professionals!


🌟 We're Expanding Our Team! 🌟

Our bustling private practice in the heart of the Central West is on the lookout for passionate dental professionals to bridge the dental health gap in our community. We have opportunities for:
General Dentists
Specialists (Endodontists, Periodontists)
Opportunities & Benefits:
Flexible Work Arrangements: Full-time or FIFO, with negotiable days and hours.
Immediate Start Needed: Our practice is in high demand, booked out five weeks ahead!
Attractive Earnings: We offer a highly competitive compensation model.
Continuing Education: Includes fully funded training, such as implant fellowships with the Australasian Implant Academy.
Clinical Autonomy & Advanced Technology: Enjoy full clinical autonomy and a fully digital workflow with onsite 3D printing and CAD/CAM.
Additional Perks:
Relocation Bonus: Available for the right candidate.
International Applicants Welcome: Encouraging applications from registered dental practitioners in Australia, the UK, and Ireland.
Visa Sponsorship & Relocation Support: Available for candidates moving from the UK, Ireland, or Scotland.
Join us to make a significant impact on our community's dental health. We can't wait to welcome you aboard! 🦷✨

If you would like to find out more about these positions please email or call me on 0407 283 253 or warrick@delroyparkdental.com.au

It was an honor to attend the Australian Dental Council Assessors, Examiners & Item Writers conference yesterday, and a Happy 30th Year Celebration 🎉 
It was also a time to say farewell to the magnificent Narelle Mills, the outstanding achievements that you have made have only made the ADC stronger and more Inclusive. A huge thank you to all my wonderful colleagues Roisin McGrath PhD Karen Smart Denise Higgins, PhD Murray Thomas Chris Bourke Martin Webb Alex Park Sonia Romeo Veronica Vele University of Melbourne Indigenous Dental Association of Australia any many others for all the hard work you do to ensure our profession keeps growing strong
